results.description: UCF was secretly the creator of the concept for Disney World. Have you ever wondered why Disney is off the charts with all of its property that it currently owns? There is no way that one organization alone managed to come up with all the ideas that it has throughout the years without having outsourced any of the projects that were necessary. This is why I am suggesting that UCF is actually responsible for the large success for Disney as a whole. It’s not just all the internships that Disney siphons off of their parent company, UCF, but all the projects it has us do. LOL we basically made SPACE MOUNTAIN for them. I mean it couldn’t be less obvious. Clearly the display at UCF’s Engineering 2 building is an apparent example of Disney World wanting to extend part of their park into the schools landscape. I mean if we were just showing off the cart that was designed by UCF students, wouldn’t we have just displayed the cart alone? The tracks are connected underground to a still present track system that most likely would have joined both UCF and Disney World together. Of course, planners realized that this would most likely botch their cover, and so they went against this decision and conveniently covered up their mid construction with a statue commemorating our students.
results.title: UCF is Disney!

results.description: Have you honestly been believing all of that fronting stories that Google is just trying to provide an internet connection to everyone in the world. Sure this all seems like fun and games, and that they are doing an amazing thing. But really, how is no one seeing what is actually going to transpire if we don’t garner ourselves in a collaborate effort to push away these oppressors. They are looking for GLOBAL DOMINATION. AND I KNOW what you’re thinking. "Oh, they may just be trying to secure the global market for internet to collect more data and stuff." WELL THAT’S FAR FROM THE TRUTH. Have you actually seen what’s inside these airships they are lazily flying around to provide WIFI??? They are transporting cargo of great importance to their plans. Specifically placed and calculated EMP pulses will turn the world into a unorganized mess and where will everyone go for their internet provisions? Google is just going to sit on top of their thrones and send out their Android army built by all that data they have collected on all of us and we won’t be able to post anything on snapchat about how my neighbor is being attacked by funny looking green robots. Who will save Mrs. Harrison? Well definitely not anyone. Google will sit back and reap all the benefits
results.title: Google Airships Begin Path To Global Domination

results.description: Look, I know UCF has a large population and that is why parking is always slims in the mornings and afternoons, but hear me out. UCF is purposely abandoning cars on the lower levels of the parking garages in order to create more issues for parking for their students. The reason??? Well they want to make sure that their students never graduate college! I swear this is the third time that I have had to take MACRO economics. They fill up the spots to make it harder to park, and therefore you keep making it to all your classes late. When this happens, teachers begin failing you on your exams because you couldn’t make it to class. Well it wasn’t my fault I lost those precious 30 minutes of class because I was stuck in parking garage D trying to find room on the ledge of the top floor. Need evidence??? Well look no further than Parking Garage A. Why are there so many cars parked their at night? It makes no sense, who is even in school at this time. These are some of their left over cars from their daily routine of parking congestion that they leave here. I’m going to the deans tomorrow about this. If you don’t hear from me after that, assume that I died and report this to the police. (Watch out, I think the police may be involved so proceed with caution)
results.title: UCF Parking Trying to make us pay more Tuition
